parsed.explanation: The main issue was incorrect nesting of <BIBL> tags, where a <BIBL> tag containing a title was immediately followed by another <BIBL> tag before the first was closed. This typically indicates a list of distinct bibliographical items that were improperly grouped. I separated these into distinct <BIBL> entries, adding closing </BIBL> tags where necessary. Additionally, where "Ejusd." (eiusdem, meaning "by the same author") was clearly implied for subsequent works after an author was explicitly named, I added the <AUTHOR>Ejusd.</AUTHOR> tag to maintain consistency and clarity for each book entry. Finally, a typographic error of <PRICE> was corrected to <PRIZE> to match the consistent tagging used for other prices.
